        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 20 at 5:11PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 511 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 6
miles southwest of Morganton, or 4 miles south of Glen Alpine, moving
south at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Morganton, Glen Alpine, and South Mountains State Park.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
